This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama in honor of Memorial Day. The proclamation recognizes the sacrifices made by American soldiers throughout history and encourages Americans to observe a National Moment of Remembrance at 3:00 p.m. local time. It also expresses appreciation for current service members and their families and asks for God's grace to protect those fighting in distant lands. The proclamation calls on Americans to preserve the legacy of fallen soldiers and work for peace, freedom, and security. It also mentions that Congress has designated Memorial Day as a day of prayer for permanent peace and requests the flag to be flown at half-staff until noon on Memorial Day.